    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wood finishing and decoration technique, creating a faux marble or stone effect, often used to make intarsia scenes or patterns with small chips or pieces of variously colored wood. The technique was made popular in 16th-17th-century German furniture making, although it is seen in later furniture as well.</Note_Text>
